<!--

Version: 0.1-Test
With this config there will be no Overpowered SAGMill recipes (1 Copper => 4 Copper Dust & 2 Gold) anymore,
just regular Ore > Crushed > Impure chain of processing. However, I love EnderIO, and I love Gregtech, 
so why not combine both?

So far:
- 2 new GrindingBalls: Diamond Head (Steel + Diamond) and Tungsten Head (Tungsten + Diamond)
- Flint only saves power
- DarkSteel Balls give the same base ouput, but a higher chance of bonus, which results in a machine that works fast,
and produces the same output as any macerator (Needs to be verified!)
- Starting with Diamond and Tungsten Grinding heads (They last for a while... values have to be changed maybe)
you will get a chance of getting even more output from your ore.

So basicly, if you have access to one or both grinding heads, you can choose to:
- Throw your ores in you pulverizer and get 2x the base ore + 10% chance for side-products
or
- Throw your ores in the SAGMill with Tungsten/Diamond head and get 2,5 to 3 times the base ores, but without side-products.

IMHO, this system should pay off for both sides (EnderIO and Gregtech people), as both ways are somewhat usefull, but they do not bypass each other

Again, this is a first draft, and the numbers and chances are most probably way too high/too low.
Also, just a few ores are available, maybe I'll add the rest later
-->


